1
00:00:01,236 --> 00:00:03,108
[grand orchestral fanfare
playing]

2
00:00:26,131 --> 00:00:28,089
♪ ♪

3
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:45,019
♪ ♪

4
00:01:00,339 --> 00:01:02,123
Can you pull over?

5
00:01:12,568 --> 00:01:13,917
[grunting]

6
00:01:15,745 --> 00:01:17,747
KENNA:
Dear Scotty:

7
00:01:17,791 --> 00:01:19,967
So, I'm out early
for good behavior,

8
00:01:20,010 --> 00:01:24,232
and here I am, stealing this.

9
00:01:24,276 --> 00:01:28,062
You always hated memorials,
and now I hate them, too.

10
00:01:29,063 --> 00:01:30,760
I hope it's not bad karma,

11
00:01:30,804 --> 00:01:34,503
because I'm headed back
to the place it all went wrong.

12
00:01:34,547 --> 00:01:37,114
See if I can
get something right.

13
00:01:44,252 --> 00:01:46,472
-[indistinct chatter]
-[baby crying]

14
00:01:54,001 --> 00:01:55,394
[grunts softly]

15
00:01:55,437 --> 00:01:56,873
[kitten meows]

16
00:01:56,917 --> 00:01:58,484
RUTH: 550 a month.
First and last today.

17
00:01:59,876 --> 00:02:00,964
No lease.

18
00:02:01,008 --> 00:02:02,270
[kittens squeaking]

19
00:02:03,358 --> 00:02:05,708
-What's your name?
-Kenna Rowan.

20
00:02:10,191 --> 00:02:12,193
[electric guitar playing
rock music in distance]

21
00:02:14,064 --> 00:02:15,892
[sighs]

22
00:02:15,936 --> 00:02:17,633
Shut it, Doug!

23
00:02:19,331 --> 00:02:20,767
-[music stops]
-DOUG: Bitch!

24
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:22,334
RUTH:
Water and sewer are covered.

25
00:02:22,377 --> 00:02:24,249
There's a $250 deposit
for electric.

26
00:02:24,292 --> 00:02:26,860
T-Two hundred and fifty
on top of two months' rent?

27
00:02:26,903 --> 00:02:28,383
And take a kitten.

28
00:02:28,427 --> 00:02:29,993
A kitten?

29
00:02:30,037 --> 00:02:32,518
Yeah, a kitten.
It's like a cat but smaller.

30
00:02:32,561 --> 00:02:35,042
-Well, I don't want a kitten.
-Who wouldn't want a kitten?

31
00:02:35,085 --> 00:02:37,087
Me.

32
00:02:40,308 --> 00:02:42,571
RUTH: I'll make you a deal.
You take a kitten,

33
00:02:42,615 --> 00:02:44,312
and I'll leave the electric on
for three weeks.

34
00:02:44,356 --> 00:02:46,140
Give you a chance
to get your shit together.

35
00:02:48,882 --> 00:02:50,144
Fine.

36
00:02:50,971 --> 00:02:52,451
Here.

37
00:02:52,494 --> 00:02:54,104
[kitten meows]

38
00:02:55,105 --> 00:02:57,151
[kitten squeaking]

39
00:02:58,239 --> 00:03:00,285
♪ ♪

40
00:03:05,028 --> 00:03:06,726
KENNA:
Remember how we used to wonder

41
00:03:06,769 --> 00:03:08,945
what this place was like?

42
00:03:08,989 --> 00:03:12,775
Well, Paradise is no paradise.

43
00:03:15,952 --> 00:03:18,607
And my new roommate
is a small cat.

44
00:03:18,651 --> 00:03:20,609
What am I gonna do with you?
[sighs]

45
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:26,441
Now I just need a job
so I can stay here,

46
00:03:26,485 --> 00:03:28,356
make this place a home.

47
00:03:37,844 --> 00:03:40,542
Maybe then
they'll let me see her.

48
00:03:40,586 --> 00:03:42,370
Yeah, well, I'm hungry, too.

49
00:03:42,414 --> 00:03:44,981
[squeaks]

50
00:03:45,025 --> 00:03:47,070
DIEM:
Did you used to paint your nails

51
00:03:47,114 --> 00:03:49,159
when you were in the MFL?

52
00:03:49,203 --> 00:03:51,031
LEDGER:
[chuckles] The NFL.

53
00:03:51,074 --> 00:03:52,946
DIEM:
Oh, NFL.

54
00:03:54,469 --> 00:03:56,558
You need to be pretty
for going to work.

55
00:03:56,602 --> 00:03:59,996
It's very, very important,
right?

56
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:02,259
Not as important
as being kind and smart.

57
00:04:02,303 --> 00:04:04,697
-Mm. If you say so.
-[chuckles softly]

58
00:04:04,740 --> 00:04:06,133
GRACE:
Diem.

59
00:04:06,176 --> 00:04:08,744
Come on, sweetie,
it's time to come home.

60
00:04:08,788 --> 00:04:10,224
You got to let Ledger
get to work.

61
00:04:10,267 --> 00:04:11,486
Finished.

62
00:04:11,530 --> 00:04:13,270
Thanks, D. [blows]

63
00:04:13,314 --> 00:04:14,359
This is perfect.

64
00:04:14,402 --> 00:04:16,099
All right, let's get you home.

65
00:04:16,143 --> 00:04:19,189
Dragons hold hands
when they cross the street.

66
00:04:19,233 --> 00:04:21,366
Dragons don't have hands, silly.
They have wings.

67
00:04:21,409 --> 00:04:23,019
[Ledger chuckles]

68
00:04:23,063 --> 00:04:24,934
-Come here. Oh!
-Oh. All right.

69
00:04:24,978 --> 00:04:26,414
Thanks.

70
00:04:26,458 --> 00:04:27,676
LEDGER:
Thanks for the visit, D.

71
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:29,417
-Love you.
-Bye. Love you, too.

72
00:04:29,461 --> 00:04:30,940
-GRACE: Gave him a manicure?
-DIEM: Hmm.

73
00:04:30,984 --> 00:04:33,073
♪ ♪

74
00:04:46,739 --> 00:04:48,175
What the...

75
00:04:52,266 --> 00:04:54,268
♪ ♪

76
00:05:01,449 --> 00:05:03,495
-Hey.

77
00:05:03,538 --> 00:05:06,280
Oh. What's got your manties
in a bunch?

78
00:05:10,327 --> 00:05:12,286
-[Mary Anne sighs]
-ROMAN: Afternoon.

79
00:05:12,329 --> 00:05:13,592
-What's up?
-Hola.

80
00:05:13,635 --> 00:05:15,245
[chuckles]:
Hey.

81
00:05:15,289 --> 00:05:17,160
-Got your favorite.
-Let me guess. Is it a mug?

82
00:05:18,814 --> 00:05:20,337
More Broncos swag? Seriously?

83
00:05:20,381 --> 00:05:22,818
-Must be Wednesday.
-[Ledger sighs]

84
00:05:22,862 --> 00:05:26,039
It might be worth
drinking again.

85
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:28,476
Just to end this torture.

86
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,869
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah.

87
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:33,002
Which mug would you use?

88
00:05:33,046 --> 00:05:34,787
STD awareness mug. Yeah.

89
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:36,832
-It's a favorite.
-[laughs] Nice choice.

90
00:05:36,876 --> 00:05:38,486
While you're obliterating
your liver,

91
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:40,357
you might as well keep
one eye on your chlamydia.

92
00:05:40,401 --> 00:05:41,446
ROMAN:
Priorities.

93
00:05:41,489 --> 00:05:43,404
-[laughter]
-Funny.

94
00:05:43,448 --> 00:05:44,579
MARY ANNE:
I thought it was funny.

95
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:48,540
So, what is it? [sniffs]

96
00:05:48,583 --> 00:05:49,976
Scotty's memorial's gone.

97
00:05:50,019 --> 00:05:51,499
-Someone took it?
-Yep.

98
00:05:53,893 --> 00:05:55,938
Who would do something
like that?

99
00:05:55,982 --> 00:05:58,680
-Do you happen to be hiring?
-No.

100
00:05:58,724 --> 00:06:00,508
[birds chirping]

101
00:06:00,552 --> 00:06:02,554
♪ ♪

102
00:06:04,294 --> 00:06:06,209
Hey, uh, are you hiring?

103
00:06:06,253 --> 00:06:08,690
-No. I'm sorry.
-Okay. Thank you.

104
00:06:08,734 --> 00:06:10,823
[entry bells jingling]

105
00:06:10,866 --> 00:06:12,346
[sighs heavily]

106
00:06:12,389 --> 00:06:13,826
Hey.

107
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,094
MRS. BURKE:
Come on in.

108
00:06:21,137 --> 00:06:22,791
[lively chatter]

109
00:06:22,835 --> 00:06:24,967
No, thanks. I just wanted
to see if you needed help.

110
00:06:25,011 --> 00:06:26,316
[sighs] Desperately.

111
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,666
[chuckles] Here, sit.

112
00:06:27,709 --> 00:06:29,232
I'll get an application.

113
00:06:29,276 --> 00:06:31,408
CHILD:
Can I have some more fries?

114
00:06:31,452 --> 00:06:33,062
["Passenger Seat" by Upstate
playing over speakers]

115
00:06:33,106 --> 00:06:35,761
-Here we go.
-Thank you.

116
00:06:35,804 --> 00:06:38,285
♪ We can wave goodbye ♪

117
00:06:38,328 --> 00:06:41,114
-♪ Honey, you can count on me ♪
-CHILD: Can I have some more?

118
00:06:41,157 --> 00:06:42,507
FATHER:
Use your fork.

119
00:06:42,550 --> 00:06:44,552
♪ Never let you down, I'll be ♪

120
00:06:44,596 --> 00:06:47,120
♪ With you
in the passenger seat ♪

121
00:06:47,163 --> 00:06:49,818
♪ Come along for the ride ♪

122
00:06:49,862 --> 00:06:51,385
♪ Anywhere you want... ♪

123
00:06:51,428 --> 00:06:53,735
Oh, we can't hire folks
with a record, hon.

124
00:06:53,779 --> 00:06:55,302
It's policy.

125
00:06:56,259 --> 00:06:57,609
Okay.

126
00:06:57,652 --> 00:07:00,350
Been burned too many times.

127
00:07:00,394 --> 00:07:01,569
Why don't you try
the Dollar Den.

128
00:07:01,613 --> 00:07:03,092
They're always looking.

129
00:07:03,136 --> 00:07:04,529
["The Night We Met"
by Lord Huron playing]

130
00:07:04,572 --> 00:07:06,574
[singers vocalizing]

131
00:07:06,618 --> 00:07:08,228
-[door opens]
-[entry bells jingling]

132
00:07:10,404 --> 00:07:12,145
Hello.

133
00:07:12,188 --> 00:07:14,539
♪ ♪

134
00:07:31,164 --> 00:07:32,644
Just that.

135
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:35,690
[clears throat]

136
00:07:35,734 --> 00:07:37,562
[register keys
clicking and beeping]

137
00:07:37,605 --> 00:07:38,693
Come back soon.

138
00:07:40,869 --> 00:07:42,479
If you insist.

139
00:07:46,092 --> 00:07:49,704
♪ I've been searching
for a trail... ♪

140
00:07:49,748 --> 00:07:51,837
You know, you can buy
more than one thing at a time.

141
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,621
Mm. Mm-hmm.

142
00:07:53,665 --> 00:07:58,583
I'm just working up the courage
to ask you out, Kenna.

143
00:08:00,672 --> 00:08:03,283
Well, um, Scotty...

144
00:08:03,326 --> 00:08:05,764
-Mm-hmm.
-...it's, um, unfortunately

145
00:08:05,807 --> 00:08:10,507
against store policy for
employees to date customers.

146
00:08:11,944 --> 00:08:13,249
Really?

147
00:08:13,293 --> 00:08:15,121
Mm-hmm.

148
00:08:15,164 --> 00:08:17,079
Can I see that?

149
00:08:17,123 --> 00:08:18,559
Excuse me.

150
00:08:18,603 --> 00:08:21,083
Um, I'd just like
to return these plates.

151
00:08:21,127 --> 00:08:22,171
CLERK:
Oh, sure.

152
00:08:22,215 --> 00:08:24,304
SCOTTY:
And, uh...

153
00:08:24,347 --> 00:08:27,437
I'm never shopping here again.

154
00:08:27,481 --> 00:08:29,657
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

155
00:08:31,485 --> 00:08:33,008
[Scotty clears throat]

156
00:08:33,052 --> 00:08:34,531
So...

157
00:08:35,924 --> 00:08:37,926
...can I take you to dinner?

158
00:08:40,059 --> 00:08:41,190
In that thing?

159
00:08:41,234 --> 00:08:43,062
You don't like it?

160
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:45,978
It's just about the ugliest
color orange I've ever seen.

161
00:08:46,021 --> 00:08:47,632
[chuckles] I know.

162
00:08:47,675 --> 00:08:51,244
It's not mine.
It's my best friend's.

163
00:08:52,245 --> 00:08:54,160
I get off at 7:00.

164
00:08:55,422 --> 00:08:57,642
-[song fades]
-[vehicle passing]

165
00:08:59,644 --> 00:09:02,864
KENNA: Everything here
reminds me of you,

166
00:09:02,908 --> 00:09:06,085
but I have to keep going.

167
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:08,174
Maybe the bookstore
we loved will help.

168
00:09:09,175 --> 00:09:11,960
I miss their bougie coffee.

169
00:09:12,004 --> 00:09:13,962
And I miss you.

170
00:09:14,006 --> 00:09:15,790
Love, Kenna.

171
00:09:18,793 --> 00:09:21,013
-♪ Ballad that you'd play ♪
-[lively chatter]

172
00:09:21,056 --> 00:09:26,801
♪ While you swore to God
the singer read your mind ♪

173
00:09:26,845 --> 00:09:31,501
♪ But the world is scared
of hesitating things ♪

174
00:09:32,981 --> 00:09:36,071
♪ Yeah, they only shoot
the birds ♪

175
00:09:36,115 --> 00:09:38,247
-♪ Who cannot sing... ♪
-[billiard balls clacking]

176
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:41,163
Who the hell turned
this bookstore into a bar?

177
00:09:41,207 --> 00:09:42,382
I did.

178
00:09:44,558 --> 00:09:46,821
[sighs] What can I get you?

179
00:09:49,563 --> 00:09:51,173
A coffee.

180
00:09:51,217 --> 00:09:54,002
Coffee? Sure.
Uh, cream and sugar okay?

181
00:09:54,046 --> 00:09:56,265
Could you do, um, caramel
and extra foam, please?

182
00:09:56,309 --> 00:09:57,484
You bet.

183
00:09:57,527 --> 00:09:59,268
Soy, skim, almond or whole milk?

184
00:09:59,312 --> 00:10:01,140
Whole's fine.

185
00:10:01,183 --> 00:10:02,881
I was kidding.

186
00:10:02,924 --> 00:10:04,273
Uh, this is a bar.

187
00:10:04,317 --> 00:10:06,667
I do have
a four-hour-old pot of coffee

188
00:10:06,711 --> 00:10:09,235
and your choice
of cream, sugar, both or none.

189
00:10:10,279 --> 00:10:11,977
I'll just take whatever.

190
00:10:13,282 --> 00:10:14,370
Okay.

191
00:10:14,414 --> 00:10:16,416
Uh... [clears throat]

192
00:10:16,459 --> 00:10:18,374
Whatever, coming right up.

193
00:10:18,418 --> 00:10:21,813
♪ I hope you marry rich ♪

194
00:10:21,856 --> 00:10:27,601
♪ I hope you're scared
of only ordinary shit ♪

195
00:10:27,644 --> 00:10:33,346
♪ Like murderers and ghosts
and cancer on your skin ♪

196
00:10:33,389 --> 00:10:38,351
♪ And not your soul
and what he might do with it ♪

197
00:10:38,394 --> 00:10:40,222
♪ Ah-oh. ♪

198
00:10:45,967 --> 00:10:48,361
["One and Only" by Dhruv
playing over speakers]

199
00:10:48,404 --> 00:10:50,755
♪ Oh, darling ♪

200
00:10:52,408 --> 00:10:54,410
♪ My words are overflowing ♪

201
00:10:56,499 --> 00:10:57,892
[women laughing and chattering]

202
00:10:57,936 --> 00:11:01,113
♪ Drenched in new emotion ♪

203
00:11:01,156 --> 00:11:03,898
♪ I gotta be
right where you are ♪

204
00:11:06,988 --> 00:11:08,685
♪ With timing... ♪

205
00:11:08,729 --> 00:11:11,645
I'll take my usual.

206
00:11:11,688 --> 00:11:12,864
I got you, Stacey.

207
00:11:12,907 --> 00:11:14,779
♪ There's no way of knowing ♪

208
00:11:16,258 --> 00:11:19,609
♪ So I'll steal this moment ♪

209
00:11:21,133 --> 00:11:23,091
♪ To tell you it
straight from the heart... ♪

210
00:11:23,135 --> 00:11:24,571
Pretty impressive for
not a coffee shop.

211
00:11:24,614 --> 00:11:26,747
Well, I'll be the judge of that.

212
00:11:30,664 --> 00:11:33,798
♪ I've got your favorite song
on play ♪

213
00:11:35,495 --> 00:11:39,542
♪ I'm reminiscing on the train ♪

214
00:11:39,586 --> 00:11:41,849
♪ Said I'm a couple... ♪

215
00:11:41,893 --> 00:11:46,245
Well, I'd probably give it, um,
a solid three stars on Yelp.

216
00:11:46,288 --> 00:11:48,551
-Three?
-Mm.

217
00:11:48,595 --> 00:11:50,727
That reaction was more like
a four, four and a half.

218
00:11:50,771 --> 00:11:53,513
Well, um, no caramel, so...

219
00:11:53,556 --> 00:11:54,731
No caramel.

220
00:11:54,775 --> 00:11:56,342
Got it. Okay.

221
00:11:56,385 --> 00:11:57,996
It's good to have something
to aim for.

222
00:11:59,649 --> 00:12:00,912
What were you writing?

223
00:12:02,348 --> 00:12:03,479
[clears throat]

224
00:12:03,523 --> 00:12:05,046
Um, nothing.

225
00:12:07,048 --> 00:12:08,354
Ooh. Uh...

226
00:12:08,397 --> 00:12:11,139
Hey, do you happen to be hiring?

227
00:12:11,183 --> 00:12:14,447
I could, um, up your Yelp game.

228
00:12:14,490 --> 00:12:15,752
[chuckles] Not right now.

229
00:12:15,796 --> 00:12:17,624
Sorry.

230
00:12:17,667 --> 00:12:20,453
STACEY: Hey, Coach.
Question about tomorrow's game.

231
00:12:20,496 --> 00:12:22,107
Uh, I'll be right back.

232
00:12:24,457 --> 00:12:25,501
What's up?

233
00:12:25,545 --> 00:12:27,329
Uh, not a good pass.

234
00:12:27,373 --> 00:12:29,462
-STACEY: I get it.
-LEDGER: Uh, yeah.

235
00:12:29,505 --> 00:12:31,856
[conversation continues
indistinctly]

236
00:12:31,899 --> 00:12:33,640
-Anyways, I got work to do,
so... -[women laughing]

237
00:12:33,683 --> 00:12:36,034
How's Skylar doing? She's good?

238
00:12:36,077 --> 00:12:38,079
[conversation continues
indistinctly]

239
00:12:42,823 --> 00:12:43,998
-Those two right there?
-Yeah.

240
00:12:44,042 --> 00:12:46,261
[door opens, closes]

241
00:12:49,264 --> 00:12:52,789
♪ Anticipation on the train ♪

242
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,008
-[sighs]
-[billiard balls clacking]

243
00:12:54,052 --> 00:12:58,926
♪ Said I'm another stop away ♪

244
00:12:58,970 --> 00:13:00,449
♪ Yeah, I'm talking... ♪

245
00:13:00,493 --> 00:13:02,495
[muffled music continues inside]

246
00:13:04,671 --> 00:13:06,368
[sniffs]

247
00:13:06,412 --> 00:13:07,848
[crickets chirping]

248
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:10,329
[gasps softly]

249
00:13:11,417 --> 00:13:13,375
[whispers]:
Oh, shit.

250
00:13:14,899 --> 00:13:16,726
["Mud" by Waxahatchee
playing over speakers]

251
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:18,990
-♪ Singing, "I'm not the one" ♪
-[lively chatter]

252
00:13:19,033 --> 00:13:21,601
♪ Not your haven at the bottom ♪

253
00:13:21,644 --> 00:13:23,733
♪ Or some
miserable companion... ♪

254
00:13:23,777 --> 00:13:25,431
Uh, I left my, um...

255
00:13:25,474 --> 00:13:27,737
-Oh, right. It's in the back.
-Oh.

256
00:13:27,781 --> 00:13:29,000
Thank you.

257
00:13:29,043 --> 00:13:32,046
♪ In your storm garbage ♪

258
00:13:32,090 --> 00:13:33,482
♪ Weather worn... ♪

259
00:13:37,269 --> 00:13:39,097
I didn't read it. [sighs]

260
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:40,228
Promise.

261
00:13:41,229 --> 00:13:43,275
-Um...
-[chuckles softly]

262
00:13:43,318 --> 00:13:45,886
I could walk you out back.
It's closer.

263
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:47,366
Okay. Yeah.

264
00:13:56,288 --> 00:13:58,899
-Um, wait, um...
-[dog barking in distance]

265
00:13:58,943 --> 00:14:00,945
[Ledger clears throat]

266
00:14:00,988 --> 00:14:02,729
[sighs] You, uh...

267
00:14:02,772 --> 00:14:04,731
you mind if I get your number?

268
00:14:05,906 --> 00:14:07,299
I... [chuckles]

269
00:14:07,342 --> 00:14:09,736
Uh, I don't have a phone.
[clears throat]

270
00:14:09,779 --> 00:14:11,303
[Ledger laughs]

271
00:14:11,346 --> 00:14:13,174
Who doesn't have a phone?

272
00:14:17,657 --> 00:14:20,877
I should, uh,
I should probably go.

273
00:14:20,921 --> 00:14:24,838
Um, you should stay.

274
00:14:24,881 --> 00:14:26,622
-[door opens]
-ROMAN: Hey, Ledger, need you
inside.

275
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:28,146
LEDGER:
One sec.

276
00:14:28,189 --> 00:14:29,277
[door closes]

277
00:14:31,497 --> 00:14:33,325
You okay?

278
00:14:33,368 --> 00:14:35,327
-I have to go.
-Yeah.

279
00:14:35,370 --> 00:14:37,285
Come back tomorrow.
I'll-I'll have that caramel.

280
00:14:37,329 --> 00:14:39,374
I just-- I can't, okay?

281
00:14:39,418 --> 00:14:40,593
Yeah.

282
00:14:40,636 --> 00:14:42,682
[breathing heavily]

283
00:14:45,815 --> 00:14:47,861
[dog barking in distance]

284
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:54,433
[squeaks]

285
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:56,478
[muffled TV chatter in distance]

286
00:15:00,178 --> 00:15:02,789
[kitten meowing]

287
00:15:07,533 --> 00:15:10,101
♪ ♪

288
00:15:24,028 --> 00:15:26,030
KENNA:
Dear Scotty:

289
00:15:26,073 --> 00:15:29,207
I met your friend Ledger today.

290
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:31,861
He didn't recognize me,
but why would he?

291
00:15:31,905 --> 00:15:34,168
It's not like we ever met.

292
00:15:34,212 --> 00:15:35,909
I'm gonna keep my distance.

293
00:15:35,952 --> 00:15:37,389
-GRACE: Happy birthday.
-PATRICK: Happy birthday.

294
00:15:37,432 --> 00:15:39,434
KENNA:
I have enough to figure out.

295
00:15:39,478 --> 00:15:41,219
Especially with Grace.

296
00:15:41,262 --> 00:15:42,829
SCOTTY: Ledger said
he was gonna be here.

297
00:15:42,872 --> 00:15:44,657
He also knew it was important.

298
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,789
It's a make-or-break game
this week.

299
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:48,704
I'm sure he wants to be here.

300
00:15:48,748 --> 00:15:50,837
There's always something.

301
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:55,233
Hey, why don't we go out,
do something fun?

302
00:15:55,276 --> 00:15:56,582
-Now?
-KENNA: I've had years

303
00:15:56,625 --> 00:15:58,410
to imagine how she must feel.

304
00:15:58,453 --> 00:15:59,933
Uh, yeah. Go. Go.

305
00:15:59,976 --> 00:16:02,457
KENNA:
She didn't want you to leave.

306
00:16:02,501 --> 00:16:03,937
We should have listened.

307
00:16:05,721 --> 00:16:07,680
[knocking on door]

308
00:16:07,723 --> 00:16:12,293
If we did, she wouldn't have
heard words like "sorry..."

309
00:16:12,337 --> 00:16:13,512
[Grace sighs]

310
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:15,992
...and "accident"

311
00:16:16,036 --> 00:16:17,603
and "didn't make it."

312
00:16:19,518 --> 00:16:21,520
You were their perfect boy.

313
00:16:23,609 --> 00:16:26,177
In a perfect world,
you'd still be alive.

314
00:16:27,917 --> 00:16:32,183
But instead, they had to live
in a world without you.

315
00:16:32,226 --> 00:16:34,446
Because of me.

316
00:16:34,489 --> 00:16:35,925
I'm the one they blame.

317
00:16:37,710 --> 00:16:39,842
And I understand why.

318
00:16:39,886 --> 00:16:41,322
JUDGE:
You have pled guilty

319
00:16:41,366 --> 00:16:44,543
to vehicular manslaughter
under the influence.

320
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:46,849
This court accepts
your guilty plea

321
00:16:46,893 --> 00:16:50,810
and sentences you
to seven years' incarceration.

322
00:16:50,853 --> 00:16:52,333
[crying softly]

323
00:16:52,377 --> 00:16:54,030
KENNA:
And yet, here I am,

324
00:16:54,074 --> 00:16:57,686
back in their lives,
asking for one thing:

325
00:16:57,730 --> 00:16:59,514
to meet our daughter.

326
00:16:59,558 --> 00:17:01,429
SINGERS [over TV]:
♪ Meow... ♪

327
00:17:01,473 --> 00:17:03,301
GRACE:
[sighs] Yes.

328
00:17:03,344 --> 00:17:04,867
-Uh, I can hold.
-[door opens]

329
00:17:04,911 --> 00:17:06,695
-LEDGER: Diem!
-[door closes]

330
00:17:06,739 --> 00:17:09,133
It's time for T-ball.
Go get dressed.

331
00:17:09,176 --> 00:17:10,351
We got to go!

332
00:17:13,398 --> 00:17:15,487
Is that Scotty's old jungle gym?

333
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:20,100
That was our spot.

334
00:17:20,144 --> 00:17:21,536
GRACE: It's what she wanted
for her birthday.

335
00:17:22,581 --> 00:17:24,844
Well, of course it is.

336
00:17:24,887 --> 00:17:27,760
DIEM:
Ledger, help me!

337
00:17:27,803 --> 00:17:30,458
I can't find my other boot.

338
00:17:30,502 --> 00:17:31,981
Boots? Wear your cleats.

339
00:17:32,025 --> 00:17:34,158
-People don't wear boots
to play T-ball. -I am.

340
00:17:34,201 --> 00:17:36,682
-I'm wearing my boots today.
-Listen to your coach.

341
00:17:36,725 --> 00:17:38,423
No burger
if you don't wear your cleats.

342
00:17:38,466 --> 00:17:40,468
-Found your other boot.
-[chuckles]

343
00:17:40,512 --> 00:17:42,818
-Is that a freakin' pigeon?
-[laughs]

344
00:17:42,862 --> 00:17:44,951
[both grunting playfully]

345
00:17:46,344 --> 00:17:48,259
[chuckles] You win.

346
00:17:48,302 --> 00:17:51,305
When's my mom getting
a bigger car?

347
00:17:51,349 --> 00:17:53,438
She drives a minivan.
How big a car does she need?

348
00:17:53,481 --> 00:17:55,701
Not Nana. My mom.

349
00:17:55,744 --> 00:17:57,442
What do you mean?

350
00:17:57,485 --> 00:18:00,140
Skylar says my mom never comes
to my T-ball games,

351
00:18:00,184 --> 00:18:01,663
but when I ask Nana,

352
00:18:01,707 --> 00:18:04,536
she says she will
when she gets a bigger car.

353
00:18:04,579 --> 00:18:06,364
Mm.

354
00:18:06,407 --> 00:18:08,627
Well, let me talk to Nana
about that, but we got to go.

355
00:18:08,670 --> 00:18:09,715
We're late.
[groaning playfully]

356
00:18:09,758 --> 00:18:12,761
[Diem laughing]

357
00:18:12,805 --> 00:18:15,634
-Her mom needs a bigger car?
-[sighs] I know.

358
00:18:15,677 --> 00:18:17,113
And I, uh...

359
00:18:17,157 --> 00:18:19,333
I'm not prepared for her
to start asking.

360
00:18:19,377 --> 00:18:20,900
I'm not ready.

361
00:18:20,943 --> 00:18:22,075
Have you thought about
telling her the truth?

362
00:18:22,118 --> 00:18:24,860
-No, she's five.
-[chuckles] Yeah.

363
00:18:27,298 --> 00:18:29,038
And she won't stop asking
till she knows.

364
00:18:29,082 --> 00:18:30,953
-[keys jangling]
-[engine starts]

365
00:18:30,997 --> 00:18:33,565
Bye. Have a good game.

366
00:18:33,608 --> 00:18:36,089
♪ ♪

367
00:18:51,713 --> 00:18:53,498
MANAGER: This is
a family-owned supermarket

368
00:18:53,541 --> 00:18:56,675
that puts our customers
on a pedestal.

369
00:18:56,718 --> 00:18:58,938
Uh, nothing is more important.

370
00:18:58,981 --> 00:19:02,942
Consequently, we have to know
at every level of interface

371
00:19:02,985 --> 00:19:05,814
that we can guarantee
our customers' happiness.

372
00:19:05,858 --> 00:19:08,034
And...

373
00:19:08,077 --> 00:19:09,427
safety.

374
00:19:09,470 --> 00:19:11,603
Okay. [sighs]

375
00:19:14,954 --> 00:19:17,435
-[grunts softly, sighs]
-[door closes]

376
00:19:17,478 --> 00:19:19,132
AMY:
Hey.

377
00:19:19,175 --> 00:19:20,916
[Amy sniffling]

378
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:22,353
Hey.

379
00:19:24,572 --> 00:19:26,008
Are you okay?

380
00:19:26,052 --> 00:19:28,402
I just... [sniffles]
rear-ended someone,

381
00:19:28,446 --> 00:19:31,275
and I don't have insurance.

382
00:19:31,318 --> 00:19:32,493
[sniffles]

383
00:19:32,537 --> 00:19:34,539
What's your trauma?

384
00:19:34,582 --> 00:19:37,498
Well, I can't get a job because
I just got out of prison.

385
00:19:37,542 --> 00:19:38,891
Really? [sniffles]

386
00:19:38,934 --> 00:19:40,414
Yep. [sighs]

387
00:19:42,286 --> 00:19:43,461
Shit, you win.

388
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:46,551
Yay, me.

389
00:19:46,594 --> 00:19:48,466
What kind of job
are you looking for?

390
00:19:48,509 --> 00:19:50,816
I mean, honestly, anything.

391
00:19:52,731 --> 00:19:55,429
Well, I can't guarantee
full-time,

392
00:19:55,473 --> 00:19:57,431
but I could give you
some shifts as a bagger.

393
00:19:58,476 --> 00:20:00,086
Manager already said no.

394
00:20:00,129 --> 00:20:01,522
I could talk to him.

395
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:05,004
-Amy Matthews.
-Kenna.

396
00:20:05,047 --> 00:20:07,485
Assistant manager,
recent rear-ender,

397
00:20:07,528 --> 00:20:09,878
in charge of checkouts
and bagging.

398
00:20:09,922 --> 00:20:11,793
-Thank you.
-I wouldn't go booking

399
00:20:11,837 --> 00:20:14,579
any trips on a private jet
this side of Christmas.

400
00:20:14,622 --> 00:20:16,929
The hours are shit,
and pay's even shittier.

401
00:20:19,235 --> 00:20:22,282
Hey, don't you live
in Paradise apartments?

402
00:20:22,326 --> 00:20:24,719
Hey, don't you live
in Paradise apartments?

403
00:20:26,852 --> 00:20:28,244
-Can you start Monday?
-[girl humming a tune]

404
00:20:28,288 --> 00:20:29,550
Yes. [sighs]

405
00:20:29,594 --> 00:20:30,812
Thank you.

406
00:20:31,944 --> 00:20:35,164
[door opens, closes]

407
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:36,775
[sighs]

408
00:20:38,646 --> 00:20:40,082
[water stops]

409
00:20:50,876 --> 00:20:52,225
[chuckles softly]

410
00:20:52,268 --> 00:20:54,314
♪ ♪

411
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:59,275
[door opens, closes]

412
00:21:09,068 --> 00:21:11,026
What's Tinder?

413
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:13,159
[laughs]

414
00:21:13,202 --> 00:21:14,726
Where'd you hear that?

415
00:21:14,769 --> 00:21:16,423
Skylar's mom said
if you have it,

416
00:21:16,467 --> 00:21:18,556
she'll break her finger.

417
00:21:18,599 --> 00:21:20,775
-[laughing]
-[snorts]

418
00:21:20,819 --> 00:21:22,864
♪ ♪

419
00:21:33,397 --> 00:21:35,442
[dog barking in distance]

420
00:21:38,227 --> 00:21:39,533
[car door closes]

421
00:21:39,577 --> 00:21:42,623
DIEM:
Nana, I'm a burger monster.

422
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:45,104
GRACE [playful voice]:
Well, you better eat the burger

423
00:21:45,147 --> 00:21:46,540
before it eats you.

424
00:21:46,584 --> 00:21:48,063
LEDGER:
Guys, I'm headed out.

425
00:21:48,107 --> 00:21:49,500
-GRACE [normal voice]: Okay,
bye.
-Love you, D.

426
00:21:49,543 --> 00:21:51,153
Love you, too.

427
00:21:55,114 --> 00:21:56,245
Hey.

428
00:21:59,423 --> 00:22:01,468
How'd you know
I lived around here?

429
00:22:02,556 --> 00:22:03,818
Um...

430
00:22:05,385 --> 00:22:07,996
Well, I'm not here to see you.

431
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,650
Then why are you here?

432
00:22:11,870 --> 00:22:13,915
♪ ♪

433
00:22:16,048 --> 00:22:17,745
You're Kenna.

434
00:22:22,446 --> 00:22:24,448
I-I need to see her.

435
00:22:26,275 --> 00:22:28,452
-Go. Right now.
-[panting]

436
00:22:30,410 --> 00:22:32,673
-This is none of your business.
-The hell it isn't.

437
00:22:32,717 --> 00:22:35,154
Ledger, please.

438
00:22:35,197 --> 00:22:37,199
Please just let me
speak to them.

439
00:22:39,854 --> 00:22:42,248
-LEDGER: Goddamn.
-You don't understand, okay?

440
00:22:42,291 --> 00:22:43,510
LEDGER:
Yeah.

441
00:22:45,599 --> 00:22:47,253
Just get inside.

442
00:22:51,387 --> 00:22:52,824
Sit.

443
00:22:52,867 --> 00:22:54,390
Sit down.

444
00:22:57,916 --> 00:22:59,395
A teething ring?

445
00:22:59,439 --> 00:23:00,832
She's five.

446
00:23:02,050 --> 00:23:03,617
What are you thinking
showing up here?

447
00:23:03,661 --> 00:23:05,401
She's my daughter.

448
00:23:05,445 --> 00:23:08,013
Diem is their daughter.
Your rights were terminated.

449
00:23:09,754 --> 00:23:11,103
Goddamn.

450
00:23:11,146 --> 00:23:13,192
[both panting]

451
00:23:15,411 --> 00:23:18,632
I'm pulling the truck in
the garage and taking you home.

452
00:23:18,676 --> 00:23:20,678
Don't move. I mean it.

453
00:23:24,420 --> 00:23:26,466
-[keys jangling]
-[door opens]

454
00:23:27,902 --> 00:23:29,251
[door closes]

455
00:23:29,295 --> 00:23:31,340
♪ ♪

456
00:23:50,229 --> 00:23:51,752
Hey.

457
00:23:52,927 --> 00:23:54,363
Hey.

458
00:23:57,323 --> 00:23:59,107
-[knocks]
-Open the door!

459
00:23:59,151 --> 00:24:00,718
Get your hands off me!

460
00:24:00,761 --> 00:24:02,241
[both grunting]

461
00:24:02,284 --> 00:24:03,634
-Get off of me.
-Calm down.

462
00:24:03,677 --> 00:24:05,244
You can't be here.

463
00:24:05,287 --> 00:24:06,637
Don't touch me.

464
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,463
-Grace, shut the door.
-What's going on?

465
00:24:07,507 --> 00:24:08,726
Everything's fine.

466
00:24:08,769 --> 00:24:10,118
Hey.

467
00:24:10,162 --> 00:24:11,685
Get in the truck.

468
00:24:13,121 --> 00:24:14,906
I'll call the police.

469
00:24:14,949 --> 00:24:16,951
[both panting]

470
00:24:26,178 --> 00:24:28,223
♪ ♪

471
00:24:53,335 --> 00:24:56,338
Coming back was a mistake.

472
00:24:56,382 --> 00:24:58,776
No one benefits from you being
in Diem's life except you.

473
00:25:00,168 --> 00:25:01,605
You're an asshole.

474
00:25:02,606 --> 00:25:04,085
Fuck you!

475
00:25:07,654 --> 00:25:09,656
[panting]

476
00:25:13,704 --> 00:25:16,010
[grunting angrily]

477
00:25:24,671 --> 00:25:25,933
[sighs]

478
00:25:25,977 --> 00:25:28,980
[pained screaming]

479
00:25:31,199 --> 00:25:33,245
[crying]

480
00:25:36,030 --> 00:25:38,206
[grunting]

481
00:25:38,250 --> 00:25:40,252
-[baby crying]
-[breathing heavily]

482
00:25:49,304 --> 00:25:51,306
[baby continues crying]

483
00:25:52,786 --> 00:25:54,788
KENNA:
Wait. Where are you taking her?

484
00:25:57,443 --> 00:25:59,271
Where is she going? No!

485
00:25:59,314 --> 00:26:00,576
[door closes]

486
00:26:01,926 --> 00:26:03,710
[soft clattering]

487
00:26:03,754 --> 00:26:04,842
[door opens]

488
00:26:07,714 --> 00:26:09,629
[door closes]

489
00:26:10,630 --> 00:26:12,893
Why don't you have any stuff?

490
00:26:12,937 --> 00:26:14,503
I just moved in.

491
00:26:19,117 --> 00:26:21,162
Can I have this?

492
00:26:22,468 --> 00:26:24,122
Sure.

493
00:26:24,165 --> 00:26:25,645
[gasps]

494
00:26:25,689 --> 00:26:27,778
You got a kitten?

495
00:26:27,821 --> 00:26:29,083
Can you go, please? [sighs]

496
00:26:29,127 --> 00:26:31,695
Mom won't let me have one.

497
00:26:31,738 --> 00:26:34,698
-What's its name?
-It doesn't have a name yet.

498
00:26:35,699 --> 00:26:37,701
[sighs]

499
00:26:37,744 --> 00:26:38,963
Why are you so poor?

500
00:26:40,007 --> 00:26:42,227
[laughs]

501
00:26:42,270 --> 00:26:45,709
I... just got out of prison.

502
00:26:45,752 --> 00:26:47,711
My dad's in prison.
Do you know him?

503
00:26:49,103 --> 00:26:51,889
I was in a women's prison,
so no.

504
00:26:51,932 --> 00:26:54,630
Why are you so sad?

505
00:26:54,674 --> 00:26:58,417
I have a daughter, and
no one's letting me see her.

506
00:26:58,460 --> 00:27:00,549
[gasps] Did she get kidnapped?

507
00:27:00,593 --> 00:27:03,291
[chuckles] No, no.

508
00:27:03,335 --> 00:27:04,684
She's with her grandparents,

509
00:27:04,728 --> 00:27:06,251
but they're not
letting me see her.

510
00:27:06,294 --> 00:27:07,643
But you want to?

511
00:27:09,297 --> 00:27:10,821
More than anything.

512
00:27:10,864 --> 00:27:12,431
I'm Lady Diana.

513
00:27:12,474 --> 00:27:13,780
I have some sparklers.

514
00:27:13,824 --> 00:27:15,434
Do you want
to light them with me?

515
00:27:17,479 --> 00:27:18,611
Maybe later?

516
00:27:23,181 --> 00:27:24,835
[door opens]

517
00:27:27,228 --> 00:27:29,448
[door closes]

518
00:27:29,491 --> 00:27:31,711
MAN:
Rec room closes in 15 minutes.

519
00:27:31,755 --> 00:27:33,104
[door buzzes]

520
00:27:35,106 --> 00:27:37,238
-[inmates chattering]
-[indistinct radio chatter]

521
00:27:41,765 --> 00:27:44,332
[indistinct announcement
over P.A.]

522
00:27:44,376 --> 00:27:46,682
Come with me. I'm Ivy.

523
00:27:49,468 --> 00:27:52,688
MAN [over P.A.]:
Rec room closes in ten minutes.

524
00:27:52,732 --> 00:27:55,517
Start heading back
to your bunks.

525
00:27:57,476 --> 00:27:59,783
Boy or girl?

526
00:28:00,784 --> 00:28:02,176
Was a girl.

527
00:28:03,482 --> 00:28:05,440
They gonna let you see her?

528
00:28:05,484 --> 00:28:08,269
MAN [over P.A.]: All inmates
and COs be advised...

529
00:28:08,313 --> 00:28:09,531
Don't know.

530
00:28:12,447 --> 00:28:14,058
[hand dryer whirring]

531
00:28:16,625 --> 00:28:18,236
They took your baby from you.

532
00:28:21,152 --> 00:28:23,023
You're never gonna
get over that.

533
00:28:24,590 --> 00:28:28,246
So, you decide,
right here, right now.

534
00:28:28,289 --> 00:28:31,162
You gonna live in your sadness
or you gonna die in it?

535
00:28:34,034 --> 00:28:35,993
I'm gonna live in it.

536
00:28:37,037 --> 00:28:38,473
[kitten squeaks]

537
00:28:41,563 --> 00:28:44,175
I'm gonna name you Ivy.

538
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,490
[Grace stammers]

539
00:28:55,534 --> 00:28:57,188
How could she just show up?

540
00:28:57,231 --> 00:28:58,580
I hope you told her
to leave town.

541
00:28:58,624 --> 00:29:00,539
-She is not welcome here.
-Of course I did.

542
00:29:00,582 --> 00:29:02,323
GRACE: I can't believe
she's out already.

543
00:29:02,367 --> 00:29:04,108
Diem almost saw her.

544
00:29:04,151 --> 00:29:05,936
Let me go say good night to D
before I head to work.

545
00:29:05,979 --> 00:29:08,852
I got to call our lawyer.

546
00:29:08,895 --> 00:29:10,941
GRACE:
Oh, God.

547
00:29:22,909 --> 00:29:24,171
You good?

548
00:29:24,215 --> 00:29:25,781
Yep.

549
00:29:28,132 --> 00:29:29,655
Kenna's back.

550
00:29:29,698 --> 00:29:32,049
-Diem's mom?
-Yep. [sighs] She was the woman

551
00:29:32,092 --> 00:29:33,702
sitting at the end of the bar
the other night.

552
00:29:33,746 --> 00:29:35,704
[chuckles] No shit.

553
00:29:35,748 --> 00:29:37,706
-You didn't recognize her?
-Nope.

554
00:29:37,750 --> 00:29:39,491
Never met her.

555
00:29:40,709 --> 00:29:42,233
I thought he was, like,
your best friend.

556
00:29:43,669 --> 00:29:45,062
[sighs]

557
00:29:45,105 --> 00:29:46,541
Yeah, but I wasn't around.

558
00:29:46,585 --> 00:29:48,543
I saw her mug shot once.

559
00:29:48,587 --> 00:29:51,938
But, uh, she looked
completely different then.

560
00:29:51,982 --> 00:29:53,809
I don't know.

561
00:29:53,853 --> 00:29:55,811
Patrick and Grace
don't need this right now.

562
00:29:59,337 --> 00:30:02,122
I mean, to be fair,
she did give birth to D.

563
00:30:02,166 --> 00:30:04,124
Yeah, but no parent should be
forced to set up visitation

564
00:30:04,168 --> 00:30:05,691
with their son's murderer.

565
00:30:05,734 --> 00:30:07,736
Don't you think "murderer"
is a bit dramatic?

566
00:30:07,780 --> 00:30:09,347
She's not
some stone-cold killer.

567
00:30:09,390 --> 00:30:11,305
She left him there.

568
00:30:11,349 --> 00:30:13,873
Ledge, if it weren't for you,

569
00:30:13,917 --> 00:30:16,049
I'd be lying
in a ditch somewhere.

570
00:30:16,093 --> 00:30:19,531
Maybe she's operating
in the same gray area I was.

571
00:30:20,662 --> 00:30:22,099
So, what, she's in the gray,

572
00:30:22,142 --> 00:30:24,318
and now you want to be
all black and white?

573
00:30:24,362 --> 00:30:26,320
It's not like you.

574
00:30:28,061 --> 00:30:29,715
Want some seeds?

575
00:30:32,152 --> 00:30:33,545
You're an asshole.

576
00:30:33,588 --> 00:30:36,113
[chuckles]

577
00:30:36,156 --> 00:30:39,159
["Bright Star"
by Anaïs Mitchell playing]

578
00:30:41,509 --> 00:30:43,033
[sighs]

579
00:30:48,690 --> 00:30:50,997
♪ Bright star ♪

580
00:30:51,041 --> 00:30:53,478
♪ I've sailed
in all directions ♪

581
00:30:53,521 --> 00:30:55,610
♪ I've followed
your reflection ♪

582
00:30:55,654 --> 00:30:58,483
♪ To the farthest
foreign shore ♪

583
00:30:58,526 --> 00:31:00,398
♪ Bright star, bright star ♪

584
00:31:00,441 --> 00:31:03,009
♪ I have anchored
in the harbor ♪

585
00:31:03,053 --> 00:31:05,664
♪ I have brought
my gifts to barter ♪

586
00:31:05,707 --> 00:31:07,622
♪ For a drifter's bed
and board ♪

587
00:31:07,666 --> 00:31:08,797
♪ Bright star ♪

588
00:31:10,974 --> 00:31:12,932
♪ I have drunk
the wine of ages ♪

589
00:31:12,976 --> 00:31:15,152
♪ In the company of strangers ♪

590
00:31:15,195 --> 00:31:17,632
♪ We have sung
in tongues of angels ♪

591
00:31:17,676 --> 00:31:20,113
♪ And then stumbled
on the pavement ♪

592
00:31:20,157 --> 00:31:22,289
♪ And I understood
my place then ♪

593
00:31:22,333 --> 00:31:24,552
♪ And my purpose in relation ♪

594
00:31:24,596 --> 00:31:27,686
♪ To the young
and ancient night. ♪

595
00:31:47,140 --> 00:31:48,446
[sighs]

596
00:31:48,489 --> 00:31:50,230
[song fades]

597
00:31:59,935 --> 00:32:01,241
Why are you here?

598
00:32:01,285 --> 00:32:02,982
I just wanted to see
if you were okay.

599
00:32:03,026 --> 00:32:04,462
[scoffs]

600
00:32:04,505 --> 00:32:05,767
Wait.

601
00:32:05,811 --> 00:32:07,682
Are you okay?

602
00:32:09,597 --> 00:32:10,903
Yeah.

603
00:32:10,946 --> 00:32:13,384
But that's not it,
really, is it?

604
00:32:13,427 --> 00:32:16,256
You're worried that if you hear
that I ended my life

605
00:32:16,300 --> 00:32:17,736
while you're eating
your cornflakes in the morning,

606
00:32:17,779 --> 00:32:19,477
you might be left
feeling guilty.

607
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,956
That it was because of you.

608
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:23,698
But don't worry. You did it.

609
00:32:23,742 --> 00:32:25,657
Your conscience is clear.

610
00:32:26,875 --> 00:32:28,703
-[sharp thump on window]
-[gasps] Oh, my God.

611
00:32:29,704 --> 00:32:30,836
Roll down the window.

612
00:32:35,493 --> 00:32:36,842
Are you Kenna's dad?

613
00:32:36,885 --> 00:32:39,671
[laughing]

614
00:32:39,714 --> 00:32:41,020
-Okay, he's...
-Uh...

615
00:32:41,064 --> 00:32:42,630
He's definitely not my dad.

616
00:32:42,674 --> 00:32:44,241
No.

617
00:32:44,284 --> 00:32:46,982
He's the guy who won't let me
meet my daughter.

618
00:32:48,245 --> 00:32:50,073
-Jerk.
-[truck door closes]

619
00:32:56,601 --> 00:32:58,907
Thank you for being on my side.

620
00:32:58,951 --> 00:33:00,735
PATRICK: Our lawyer
told us there's nothing

621
00:33:00,779 --> 00:33:01,954
she can do legally.

622
00:33:01,997 --> 00:33:03,782
Legally is not the issue.

623
00:33:03,825 --> 00:33:06,611
I'm worried she's gonna swipe
her when no one's looking.

624
00:33:06,654 --> 00:33:08,787
PATRICK:
We can't trust her.

625
00:33:08,830 --> 00:33:11,311
I don't know. I don't think
she'd do something like that.

626
00:33:13,618 --> 00:33:15,141
Wh-What do you mean? [stammers]

627
00:33:15,185 --> 00:33:16,664
How would you know
what she would do?

628
00:33:16,708 --> 00:33:18,710
We don't know
what she's capable of.

629
00:33:18,753 --> 00:33:22,627
None of us know her, right?

630
00:33:22,670 --> 00:33:25,760
Maybe you should meet up with
her, see what she has to say?

631
00:33:25,804 --> 00:33:28,937
[scoffs] What would
she possibly have to s-say?

632
00:33:28,981 --> 00:33:30,939
PATRICK:
Ledge, no. She's got no rights.

633
00:33:30,983 --> 00:33:34,595
-Y-You know how hard this
has been, okay? -[Grace sighs]

634
00:33:36,641 --> 00:33:39,209
We're finally in a good place.

635
00:33:39,252 --> 00:33:43,082
We're not sharing Scotty's
daughter with the woman...

636
00:33:43,126 --> 00:33:46,085
My horse's head came off.

637
00:33:46,129 --> 00:33:47,434
-PATRICK: Uh-oh.
-Oh, boy.

638
00:33:47,478 --> 00:33:49,175
-[chuckles]
-How did that happen?

639
00:33:49,219 --> 00:33:50,742
I pulled it off.

640
00:33:50,785 --> 00:33:52,657
GRACE: Yeah. Well,
it's not a surprise, then.

641
00:33:52,700 --> 00:33:54,180
Here, let's go.

642
00:33:56,313 --> 00:33:59,403
Sorry, Patrick,
I didn't mean to overstep.

643
00:33:59,446 --> 00:34:01,796
No, no, no.
Just make yourself useful.

644
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:04,321
No worries.
Just bring that wood over.

645
00:34:04,364 --> 00:34:05,452
Yes, sir.

646
00:34:10,544 --> 00:34:13,112
You want to know
something funny?

647
00:34:13,156 --> 00:34:15,245
You know Scotty had
his first kiss up here?

648
00:34:16,289 --> 00:34:17,682
Yeah, he told me that.

649
00:34:17,725 --> 00:34:18,944
Who was it? Dana?

650
00:34:18,987 --> 00:34:20,206
Yep. [sighs]

651
00:34:20,250 --> 00:34:22,339
I remember I was pissed.

652
00:34:22,382 --> 00:34:23,905
Called dibs on her first.

653
00:34:23,949 --> 00:34:25,603
Well, he's much better looking
than you are.

654
00:34:25,646 --> 00:34:26,647
[both chuckle]

655
00:34:26,691 --> 00:34:29,259
Yeah. He was.

656
00:34:31,565 --> 00:34:33,828
[Ledger sighs]

657
00:34:33,872 --> 00:34:35,308
I'm gonna get a beer.
You want one?

658
00:34:35,352 --> 00:34:36,396
Yeah, I'll take one.

659
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:38,442
♪ ♪

660
00:34:41,967 --> 00:34:43,490
[Scotty laughs]

661
00:34:43,534 --> 00:34:44,883
LEDGER:
When I'm older...

662
00:34:44,926 --> 00:34:46,450
SCOTTY:
Uh-huh.

663
00:34:46,493 --> 00:34:49,583
...I'm gonna put the "L" in NFL.

664
00:34:51,106 --> 00:34:52,804
-I hate you so much.
-[snickering]

665
00:34:54,066 --> 00:34:55,110
Team?

666
00:34:55,154 --> 00:34:57,069
[inhales deeply]

667
00:34:57,112 --> 00:34:58,505
Broncos.

668
00:34:58,549 --> 00:35:01,073
Now you're talking.

669
00:35:01,116 --> 00:35:02,770
I'm more of
a simple-life kind of guy.

670
00:35:02,814 --> 00:35:05,120
My plan is to get married,
be a dad.

671
00:35:06,513 --> 00:35:07,949
That's what I'm gonna do.

672
00:35:07,993 --> 00:35:10,909
While you go off
and take down Brady.

673
00:35:11,823 --> 00:35:13,128
Wait.

674
00:35:14,826 --> 00:35:17,045
-What?
-What is that?

675
00:35:17,089 --> 00:35:18,308
What?

676
00:35:19,309 --> 00:35:20,440
What the hell?

677
00:35:20,484 --> 00:35:22,225
SCOTTY:
What?

678
00:35:22,268 --> 00:35:24,314
Is that a freakin' pigeon?

679
00:35:26,577 --> 00:35:28,709
That?

680
00:35:28,753 --> 00:35:30,058
Yes.

681
00:35:31,669 --> 00:35:34,498
-[laughing]: A freakin' pigeon?
-[laughing]

682
00:35:34,541 --> 00:35:37,109
That's my baseball glove.

683
00:35:37,152 --> 00:35:39,459
[both laughing]

684
00:35:39,503 --> 00:35:42,157
That's my freakin'
baseball glove.

685
00:35:42,201 --> 00:35:43,811
-Holy-- Oh!
-[gasps]

686
00:35:43,855 --> 00:35:45,900
[both laughing]

687
00:35:45,944 --> 00:35:48,120
And who says "freakin'," anyway?

688
00:35:49,121 --> 00:35:51,428
You're so freakin' high.

689
00:35:53,256 --> 00:35:55,258
-[indistinct chatter]
-[scanners beeping]

690
00:35:59,610 --> 00:36:01,002
Oh, super!

691
00:36:06,573 --> 00:36:08,575
♪ ♪

692
00:36:32,773 --> 00:36:34,297
Kenna, I need you on two.

693
00:36:39,867 --> 00:36:41,782
Do you have bags?

694
00:36:41,826 --> 00:36:43,393
No bags.

695
00:36:45,699 --> 00:36:47,701
♪ ♪

696
00:37:12,639 --> 00:37:14,424
Does she look like me?

697
00:37:14,467 --> 00:37:15,903
[Ledger sighs]

698
00:37:15,947 --> 00:37:17,992
Yeah, she does.

699
00:37:18,993 --> 00:37:20,908
What's she like?

700
00:37:28,481 --> 00:37:30,091
-[Kenna sighs]
-[thunder rumbling]

701
00:37:33,704 --> 00:37:35,314
Do you walk to work?

702
00:37:35,358 --> 00:37:37,011
Yeah.

703
00:37:37,055 --> 00:37:38,099
Got an umbrella?

704
00:37:38,143 --> 00:37:39,884
Nope.

705
00:37:39,927 --> 00:37:41,451
You could call a Uber. [sighs]

706
00:37:41,494 --> 00:37:43,191
Did they have Uber before you...

707
00:37:43,235 --> 00:37:44,758
Went to prison? Yeah.

708
00:37:44,802 --> 00:37:46,151
Yeah, they had Uber.

709
00:37:47,152 --> 00:37:49,023
Still don't have a phone.

710
00:37:49,067 --> 00:37:50,373
[Ledger clears throat]

711
00:37:50,416 --> 00:37:52,418
Jerk.

712
00:37:52,462 --> 00:37:54,899
[Kenna laughing]

713
00:37:57,728 --> 00:37:59,207
[Ledger clears throat]

714
00:37:59,251 --> 00:38:02,254
["Stand by Me" by
Stephen Wilson Jr. playing]

715
00:38:04,474 --> 00:38:06,998
♪ When the night ♪

716
00:38:07,041 --> 00:38:09,348
♪ The night has come ♪

717
00:38:09,392 --> 00:38:11,089
[thunder rumbling softly]

718
00:38:11,132 --> 00:38:13,874
♪ And all the land is dark ♪

719
00:38:13,918 --> 00:38:16,181
♪ And the moon ♪

720
00:38:16,224 --> 00:38:20,925
♪ Is the only light we'll see ♪

721
00:38:23,101 --> 00:38:27,758
♪ No, I won't be afraid ♪

722
00:38:27,801 --> 00:38:32,415
♪ No, I won't shed
a single tear ♪

723
00:38:32,458 --> 00:38:36,767
♪ Just as long as you,
just as long as you ♪

724
00:38:36,810 --> 00:38:41,685
♪ Stand by me ♪

725
00:38:41,728 --> 00:38:44,035
-[gasps]
-♪ So won't you stand ♪

726
00:38:44,078 --> 00:38:46,994
♪ By me? ♪

727
00:38:47,038 --> 00:38:50,345
♪ Won't you, won't you ♪

728
00:38:50,389 --> 00:38:55,612
♪ Stand by me, stand by me? ♪

729
00:38:55,655 --> 00:38:57,091
♪ Won't you stand... ♪

730
00:38:57,135 --> 00:38:59,180
[breathing heavily]

731
00:39:03,968 --> 00:39:06,536
["Deep in Love" by
Bonny Light Horseman playing]

732
00:39:06,579 --> 00:39:08,668
Is that a freakin' pigeon?

733
00:39:08,712 --> 00:39:11,497
♪ Deep to the line... ♪

734
00:39:11,541 --> 00:39:12,629
You okay?

735
00:39:12,672 --> 00:39:13,847
[sighs]

736
00:39:13,891 --> 00:39:15,675
Just a little bit of rain.

737
00:39:15,719 --> 00:39:17,895
-You need a ride home?
-No, I'm fine.

738
00:39:17,938 --> 00:39:20,071
I'll just wait it out.

739
00:39:20,114 --> 00:39:22,465
It's a slow night.
Let me give you a ride.

740
00:39:22,508 --> 00:39:24,467
It's fine. [sighs]

741
00:39:24,510 --> 00:39:26,294
[chuckles]

742
00:39:26,338 --> 00:39:27,774
All right.

743
00:39:29,254 --> 00:39:30,777
♪ Break my heart... ♪

744
00:39:30,821 --> 00:39:32,605
[sighs]

745
00:39:34,868 --> 00:39:36,914
No wonder no one's in here.

746
00:39:36,957 --> 00:39:38,568
The music's miserable.

747
00:39:38,611 --> 00:39:41,179
I thought misery loved company.

748
00:39:41,222 --> 00:39:43,834
Misery loves no music
because all music is miserable.

749
00:39:43,877 --> 00:39:45,531
But I heard
misery loves caramel.

750
00:39:47,620 --> 00:39:49,448
Oh, could I get it
in a to-go cup?

751
00:39:49,492 --> 00:39:51,624
Don't push it.
Still not a coffee shop.

752
00:39:52,669 --> 00:39:54,497
Are you sure
you don't want a ride?

753
00:39:59,806 --> 00:40:01,634
Did you show up
to my bar that night

754
00:40:01,678 --> 00:40:04,071
because you wanted me
to lead you to her?

755
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:07,771
No, I only showed up

756
00:40:07,814 --> 00:40:10,121
because it was the bookstore
Scotty and I loved.

757
00:40:10,164 --> 00:40:12,297
I had no idea who you were
until I heard your name,

758
00:40:12,340 --> 00:40:14,429
because you were never around.

759
00:40:14,473 --> 00:40:15,692
[Kenna sniffles]

760
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:23,395
So you're telling me...

761
00:40:23,438 --> 00:40:24,962
What?

762
00:40:25,005 --> 00:40:26,616
Scotty knew what a book was?

763
00:40:28,313 --> 00:40:29,444
[chuckles]

764
00:40:31,359 --> 00:40:33,536
Thank you for the ride.
And the caramel.

765
00:40:39,106 --> 00:40:41,065
LEDGER: Did you say
you're going to propose?

766
00:40:41,108 --> 00:40:43,241
SCOTTY [over phone]:
You heard me correct.

767
00:40:43,284 --> 00:40:46,244
[chuckles] Don't you think
it's a little too soon?

768
00:40:46,287 --> 00:40:47,811
No. No, I don't think
it's too soon.

769
00:40:47,854 --> 00:40:49,073
I love her.

770
00:40:49,116 --> 00:40:50,901
I'm gonna ask her
on my birthday,

771
00:40:50,944 --> 00:40:52,903
-and I want you to be
there. Okay?
-MAN: Hey, two-seven.

772
00:40:52,946 --> 00:40:54,165
-Let's make moves.
-SCOTTY: Ledge.

773
00:40:54,208 --> 00:40:55,645
Hey, hey.

774
00:40:55,688 --> 00:40:57,429
Promise me.

775
00:40:57,472 --> 00:40:58,909
You're gonna love her.

776
00:40:58,952 --> 00:41:00,475
I promise I'll be there.
I got to run, all right?

777
00:41:00,519 --> 00:41:01,912
All right. Bye.

778
00:41:08,092 --> 00:41:09,615
LEDGER:
What'd you say?

779
00:41:09,659 --> 00:41:11,922
DIEM [over phone]:
What are you doing?

780
00:41:12,923 --> 00:41:14,402
Working.

781
00:41:14,446 --> 00:41:16,883
No, you're not.
You're drinking a soda.

782
00:41:16,927 --> 00:41:18,363
[sighs] What do you know
about work?

783
00:41:18,406 --> 00:41:20,495
-How many jobs have you had?
-[chuckles]

784
00:41:20,539 --> 00:41:22,149
I'm a kid!

785
00:41:22,193 --> 00:41:23,542
And what are you up to, kid?

786
00:41:23,586 --> 00:41:26,023
Going grocery shopping
with Nana.

787
00:41:26,066 --> 00:41:28,025
Oh, yeah? What store?

788
00:41:29,461 --> 00:41:31,724
What s-- Diem! [sighs]

789
00:41:33,378 --> 00:41:35,598
[line ringing]

790
00:41:35,641 --> 00:41:37,643
♪ ♪

791
00:41:46,739 --> 00:41:48,349
[tires squealing]

792
00:41:54,834 --> 00:41:56,836
-[indistinct chatter]
-[scanners beeping]

793
00:41:58,272 --> 00:42:00,448
-What are we gonna get
on our fruit platter? -Cheese.

794
00:42:00,492 --> 00:42:02,102
-Cheese on our fruit platter?
-[chuckles]

795
00:42:06,237 --> 00:42:08,021
[tires squealing]

796
00:42:10,415 --> 00:42:11,721
Grace!

797
00:42:11,764 --> 00:42:13,897
-Ledger!
-Hold up! Hold up, hold up.

798
00:42:13,940 --> 00:42:15,942
-What?
-Get her back to the car. Now.

799
00:42:15,986 --> 00:42:17,901
-Come on. Come on. Come on.
-I can walk, you know.

800
00:42:17,944 --> 00:42:20,207
♪ ♪

801
00:42:27,388 --> 00:42:29,086
Grace!

802
00:42:29,129 --> 00:42:30,174
Grace, please!

803
00:42:30,217 --> 00:42:32,002
[tires screech]

804
00:42:32,045 --> 00:42:33,568
Please!

805
00:42:38,051 --> 00:42:39,618
[grunts] Why did you do that?!

806
00:42:39,662 --> 00:42:41,315
Why the hell did you do that?!

807
00:42:41,359 --> 00:42:43,230
[panting]

808
00:42:43,274 --> 00:42:45,145
AMY:
Everything okay?

809
00:42:46,973 --> 00:42:48,105
Just go.

810
00:42:50,847 --> 00:42:53,023
-You need to take some time?
-I'm sorry. I...

811
00:42:57,810 --> 00:42:59,203
I'll deal with him.

812
00:42:59,246 --> 00:43:01,379
-I'll see you tomorrow.
-Okay. [sniffles]

813
00:43:01,422 --> 00:43:03,860
[panting]

814
00:43:03,903 --> 00:43:05,383
Thank you.

815
00:43:14,958 --> 00:43:16,960
♪ ♪

816
00:43:26,709 --> 00:43:28,145
Kenna!

817
00:43:28,188 --> 00:43:30,408
Kenna. Get in.

818
00:43:32,149 --> 00:43:34,412
Kenna. Can we talk?

819
00:43:46,990 --> 00:43:48,556
[Ledger sighs]

820
00:43:50,820 --> 00:43:52,038
[Kenna sniffles]

821
00:44:02,657 --> 00:44:05,051
Other mothers told me
what it would be like.

822
00:44:08,228 --> 00:44:13,190
I'd be taken to the hospital
to give birth

823
00:44:13,233 --> 00:44:15,714
and that I would get
two days with her.

824
00:44:18,761 --> 00:44:21,154
Two whole days, just me and her.

825
00:44:23,069 --> 00:44:25,506
It was the only thing
I had to look forward to.

826
00:44:27,726 --> 00:44:29,293
[sighs]

827
00:44:29,336 --> 00:44:31,512
But she was born early.
Um, six weeks.

828
00:44:31,556 --> 00:44:33,558
I don't know if you knew that.

829
00:44:36,256 --> 00:44:37,823
Her lungs weren't
fully developed,

830
00:44:37,867 --> 00:44:40,086
so they rushed her to the NICU.

831
00:44:42,610 --> 00:44:44,743
While I had to spend
those two days alone.

832
00:44:44,787 --> 00:44:46,005
[sniffles]

833
00:44:48,486 --> 00:44:50,357
I never got to hold her.

834
00:44:52,359 --> 00:44:54,579
-Kenna, I...
-Please don't.

835
00:44:59,018 --> 00:45:00,193
[sniffles]

836
00:45:00,237 --> 00:45:04,719
It was stupid to...

837
00:45:04,763 --> 00:45:09,072
assume that they would just
let me be a part of her life.

838
00:45:12,423 --> 00:45:15,165
I didn't come here because
I think that I deserve her.

839
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:23,695
But, God, I just...

840
00:45:23,738 --> 00:45:24,957
[sniffles]

841
00:45:26,785 --> 00:45:29,179
I want to meet the human that...

842
00:45:32,051 --> 00:45:34,053
...that Scotty and I made.

843
00:45:38,101 --> 00:45:40,407
[sniffles, sighs]

844
00:45:42,540 --> 00:45:44,150
[sighs]

845
00:45:48,067 --> 00:45:49,329
[sniffles]

846
00:45:54,987 --> 00:45:57,120
[sighs heavily]

847
00:46:03,343 --> 00:46:05,128
[inhales deeply]

848
00:46:06,651 --> 00:46:09,654
Ants in my pants
make my belly button dance.

849
00:46:09,697 --> 00:46:11,656
-Your turn, Ledger.
-[Kenna chuckles]

850
00:46:11,699 --> 00:46:14,920
Say, "Ants in my pants
make my belly button dance."

851
00:46:14,964 --> 00:46:16,443
LEDGER [over video]:
All right.

852
00:46:16,487 --> 00:46:17,967
-Ants in my pants
make my belly... -[chuckles]

853
00:46:18,010 --> 00:46:19,707
DIEM: It's a good thing
that I made you...

854
00:46:19,751 --> 00:46:22,058
made you check
your belly button, right?

855
00:46:22,101 --> 00:46:23,363
LEDGER [over video]:
Oh. Whoa.

856
00:46:23,407 --> 00:46:25,191
What you doing? All right.

857
00:46:25,235 --> 00:46:27,541
-Oh! Don't fall.
-[chuckles, sniffles]

858
00:46:28,542 --> 00:46:30,675
Mmm. Aw.

859
00:46:32,982 --> 00:46:34,766
[breathing heavily]

860
00:46:34,809 --> 00:46:36,855
[sniffles] She's amazing.

861
00:46:39,684 --> 00:46:40,903
Thank you.

862
00:46:41,947 --> 00:46:44,602
-Yeah.
-[sniffles]

863
00:46:44,645 --> 00:46:46,647
DIEM: It's a good thing
that I made you...

864
00:46:46,691 --> 00:46:49,172
-made you check your belly
button, right? -[both chuckle]

865
00:46:49,215 --> 00:46:51,217
♪ ♪

866
00:47:02,576 --> 00:47:04,230
Can I ask you something?

867
00:47:05,275 --> 00:47:06,972
Do you hate me?

868
00:47:11,585 --> 00:47:13,805
You know, the...

869
00:47:13,848 --> 00:47:16,764
other night
when we met at the bar,

870
00:47:16,808 --> 00:47:19,767
I thought you were,
I don't know, intriguing.

871
00:47:21,769 --> 00:47:24,511
Then the next day in front of
Patrick and Grace's, I...

872
00:47:26,818 --> 00:47:29,125
...thought you were
the worst person ever.

873
00:47:31,649 --> 00:47:33,564
And what about now?

874
00:47:36,523 --> 00:47:38,221
Now... [sighs]

875
00:47:40,005 --> 00:47:41,441
I'm starting to wonder

876
00:47:41,485 --> 00:47:42,747
if you're the saddest girl
I've ever met.

877
00:47:44,967 --> 00:47:47,186
All of the above, I guess.

878
00:47:47,230 --> 00:47:48,709
[chuckles softly, sniffles]

879
00:47:54,367 --> 00:47:57,022
Yeah, we should, uh...

880
00:47:57,066 --> 00:47:59,590
I'll take the...
Are you done with that?

881
00:48:05,117 --> 00:48:06,727
[Ledger sighs]

882
00:48:10,993 --> 00:48:12,472
[engine starts]

883
00:48:18,826 --> 00:48:20,872
It wasn't a good look, you know.

884
00:48:22,134 --> 00:48:24,093
Uh, to his parents,
to the judge,

885
00:48:24,136 --> 00:48:28,053
to anybody in that courtroom.

886
00:48:28,097 --> 00:48:30,621
They told me
you just seemed so...

887
00:48:30,664 --> 00:48:32,579
I seemed so what?

888
00:48:34,233 --> 00:48:35,843
Unremorseful.

889
00:48:37,802 --> 00:48:39,804
Unremorseful?

890
00:48:43,025 --> 00:48:44,461
I was broken.

891
00:48:46,898 --> 00:48:50,293
Scotty was the closest thing
to a home that I ever had.

892
00:48:56,429 --> 00:48:58,475
♪ ♪

893
00:49:18,625 --> 00:49:21,237
Sometimes I get the urge
to take her.

894
00:49:22,368 --> 00:49:23,935
You know?

895
00:49:26,981 --> 00:49:29,375
But obviously
I'm not gonna do that.

896
00:49:29,419 --> 00:49:32,987
I... just want to prove
to Grace and Patrick

897
00:49:33,031 --> 00:49:34,989
that I'm responsible.

898
00:49:36,513 --> 00:49:38,950
Well, I want to be ready
for when they let me meet her.

899
00:49:38,993 --> 00:49:41,909
And what if that day
doesn't come?

900
00:49:43,607 --> 00:49:45,609
Well, I have to live
in hope that it will.

901
00:49:47,350 --> 00:49:50,353
But I can, uh,
barely pay my rent.

902
00:49:52,006 --> 00:49:53,660
[sighs] Yeah.

903
00:49:55,271 --> 00:49:57,055
Um... [sniffs]

904
00:49:58,100 --> 00:50:00,580
What if you come
and work for me?

905
00:50:01,581 --> 00:50:02,887
For you?

906
00:50:02,930 --> 00:50:04,932
Fridays and Saturdays.

907
00:50:04,976 --> 00:50:07,805
Um, obviously in the back.
That way, no one has to know.

908
00:50:07,848 --> 00:50:09,894
Are you being serious?

909
00:50:11,287 --> 00:50:13,245
Yes.

910
00:50:13,289 --> 00:50:14,377
-[Kenna sniffles]
-Okay.

911
00:50:14,420 --> 00:50:15,987
Hey, come at 4:00 on Friday.

912
00:50:16,030 --> 00:50:19,077
["September Fields"
by Frazey Ford playing]

913
00:50:30,784 --> 00:50:32,134
[sighs]

914
00:50:33,570 --> 00:50:38,575
♪ You better get up
for your mama ♪

915
00:50:41,621 --> 00:50:46,539
♪ You better grab
the best of your life ♪

916
00:50:48,367 --> 00:50:50,804
♪ I know you're ready ♪

917
00:50:52,676 --> 00:50:55,722
♪ To get older ♪

918
00:50:57,202 --> 00:50:59,465
♪ Anyhow... ♪

919
00:51:02,251 --> 00:51:04,122
RUTH: Sick of having
this conversation with you.

920
00:51:04,166 --> 00:51:07,343
DOUG: You do nothing
but complain and complain.

921
00:51:07,386 --> 00:51:09,388
You can't evict me
for making art.

922
00:51:09,432 --> 00:51:11,260
Electric guitar at midnight
isn't art.

923
00:51:11,303 --> 00:51:12,957
It's a violation of your lease.

924
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:15,351
I didn't sign a lease.

925
00:51:15,394 --> 00:51:17,004
Did you sign anything
when you moved in?

926
00:51:17,048 --> 00:51:19,050
RUTH:
You leave her out of it, Doug.

927
00:51:19,093 --> 00:51:20,443
She took a kitten.
The rules don't apply.

928
00:51:20,486 --> 00:51:22,184
As long as
I keep paying my rent,

929
00:51:22,227 --> 00:51:24,098
I'm gonna keep playing
my guitar.

930
00:51:24,142 --> 00:51:26,623
Maybe if you play something she
likes, she won't get as mad.

931
00:51:26,666 --> 00:51:29,756
She was born mad.

932
00:51:29,800 --> 00:51:31,715
-I like the ukulele!
-DOUG: You would.

933
00:51:31,758 --> 00:51:33,238
[laughs]

934
00:51:33,282 --> 00:51:36,589
♪ And turn and turn at night? ♪

935
00:51:38,504 --> 00:51:41,377
♪ And are you holding ♪

936
00:51:41,420 --> 00:51:45,468
-♪ Holding on so tight? ♪
-[song fades]

937
00:51:45,511 --> 00:51:47,513
♪ ♪

938
00:51:53,954 --> 00:51:55,391
-[panting]
-[knocks]

939
00:51:58,742 --> 00:52:01,788
Hey, I'm Kenna.
Uh, reporting for duty.

940
00:52:02,789 --> 00:52:04,530
I'm sorry, I forgot to tell you.

941
00:52:04,574 --> 00:52:06,880
She's gonna help us out
in the back. Um...

942
00:52:08,926 --> 00:52:11,798
Uh, this is Roman. Um...

943
00:52:15,193 --> 00:52:16,499
ROMAN:
Okay.

944
00:52:16,542 --> 00:52:18,762
Uh, unexpected.

945
00:52:23,114 --> 00:52:26,944
Um, do you... do you know
how to wash dishes?

946
00:52:26,987 --> 00:52:29,163
Six years' experience.

947
00:52:29,207 --> 00:52:31,992
Okay. I'm not... I'm not gonna
ask you to elaborate on that.

948
00:52:32,036 --> 00:52:33,603
LEDGER:
I'm sorry, I got to go.

949
00:52:33,646 --> 00:52:35,300
Um, can you show her around?

950
00:52:36,345 --> 00:52:38,303
I'll be back. [sighs]

951
00:52:39,391 --> 00:52:41,350
-Follow me. This way.
-Okay.

952
00:52:41,393 --> 00:52:43,613
-[lively chatter] -♪ Yeah,
when you're giving me love... ♪

953
00:52:45,832 --> 00:52:48,835
[music and chatter continue
faintly in distance]

954
00:52:57,017 --> 00:53:00,151
Wow. I haven't seen this floor
in a long-ass time.

955
00:53:00,194 --> 00:53:02,588
-Or my shoes, for that matter.
-[chuckles]

956
00:53:02,632 --> 00:53:05,243
-Uh, do you want a drink?
-Yeah.

957
00:53:05,287 --> 00:53:07,071
-Okay.
-Thank you.

958
00:53:07,114 --> 00:53:08,899
-Whew! Oh, man.
-[can opens]

959
00:53:08,942 --> 00:53:10,509
Can I ask you something?

960
00:53:10,553 --> 00:53:11,902
Mm-hmm.

961
00:53:11,945 --> 00:53:15,819
Who is this, uh, Leah?

962
00:53:15,862 --> 00:53:20,345
Leah is Ledger's ex-fiancée.

963
00:53:20,389 --> 00:53:22,565
They broke up about a year ago.

964
00:53:22,608 --> 00:53:26,351
Wow. I had no idea. [sighs]

965
00:53:26,395 --> 00:53:28,832
She wanted to be
the only girl in his life.

966
00:53:28,875 --> 00:53:31,617
-He cheated?
-No.

967
00:53:31,661 --> 00:53:33,706
She was jealous of Diem.

968
00:53:33,750 --> 00:53:35,752
Diem's like
his-his pseudo niece.

969
00:53:35,795 --> 00:53:37,797
It's hard to explain.

970
00:53:37,841 --> 00:53:41,366
But he is hopelessly devoted
to that little girl.

971
00:53:42,976 --> 00:53:44,500
MARY ANNE: ...hang out
at my place sometime?

972
00:53:44,543 --> 00:53:46,371
[Kenna chuckles]

973
00:53:46,415 --> 00:53:48,417
MARY ANNE:
It's my third.

974
00:53:48,460 --> 00:53:50,070
When you meet my husband,
you'll know why.

975
00:53:50,114 --> 00:53:51,811
He's a lightning rod.

976
00:53:55,772 --> 00:53:58,383
Kenna has revolutionized
this place.

977
00:53:58,427 --> 00:54:00,298
ROMAN: And she found
the Cold Creek order.

978
00:54:00,342 --> 00:54:01,778
LEDGER:
Oh. This is good.

979
00:54:01,821 --> 00:54:03,867
This is great, actually. Thanks.

980
00:54:05,303 --> 00:54:06,739
Roman, I'm leaving you to close.

981
00:54:06,783 --> 00:54:09,089
-That cool?
-Yep.

982
00:54:09,133 --> 00:54:11,788
Uh, need a ride home?

983
00:54:11,831 --> 00:54:13,746
Yeah, sure.

984
00:54:13,790 --> 00:54:15,835
How come her job
comes with perks?

985
00:54:18,011 --> 00:54:19,578
See you, guys.

986
00:54:19,622 --> 00:54:22,146
-He ever give you a ride home?
-No.

987
00:54:22,189 --> 00:54:24,191
♪ ♪

988
00:54:34,419 --> 00:54:36,421
Does she ever ask about me?

989
00:54:41,470 --> 00:54:44,124
She doesn't really understand
family dynamics yet,

990
00:54:44,168 --> 00:54:47,780
so she doesn't really think
anyone's missing from her life.

991
00:54:47,824 --> 00:54:50,870
Right now, she thinks
you're not in her life because

992
00:54:50,914 --> 00:54:52,698
your car's not big enough.
[chuckles]

993
00:54:52,742 --> 00:54:54,091
What?

994
00:54:54,134 --> 00:54:55,397
[laughs]:
Yeah, I know.

995
00:54:55,440 --> 00:54:57,660
It's, uh... it's a long story.

996
00:54:59,879 --> 00:55:01,490
Can you tell me what she's like?

997
00:55:03,143 --> 00:55:04,362
She loves animals.

998
00:55:05,885 --> 00:55:08,322
Especially dogs.

999
00:55:08,366 --> 00:55:11,761
She hates peanut butter
but loves snow cones.

1000
00:55:12,762 --> 00:55:14,720
And she...

1001
00:55:14,764 --> 00:55:17,375
she has a fiery spirit.

1002
00:55:17,419 --> 00:55:18,724
Just like you.

1003
00:55:27,907 --> 00:55:30,040
I'm sorry about, uh...

1004
00:55:30,083 --> 00:55:33,260
is it Leah?

1005
00:55:33,304 --> 00:55:36,438
-Wow. Mary Anne works fast.
-Mm.

1006
00:55:36,481 --> 00:55:40,703
To be fair, um, I learned
most of my info from Scotty.

1007
00:55:40,746 --> 00:55:42,008
Oh, yeah? Like what?

1008
00:55:43,096 --> 00:55:44,707
Well, I know that you both cried

1009
00:55:44,750 --> 00:55:46,709
watching Princess Diaries.

1010
00:55:46,752 --> 00:55:48,014
Oh, my God.

1011
00:55:48,058 --> 00:55:50,103
[Kenna laughs]

1012
00:55:50,147 --> 00:55:53,193
He would always say
that catchphrase.

1013
00:55:53,237 --> 00:55:55,935
It's... "damn pigeon,"
or something.

1014
00:55:55,979 --> 00:55:57,284
It's actually "freakin' pigeon."

1015
00:55:57,328 --> 00:55:58,634
[laughs]

1016
00:56:01,288 --> 00:56:02,986
Now we're uneven.

1017
00:56:03,029 --> 00:56:04,988
I need to know more on you.

1018
00:56:06,163 --> 00:56:08,861
What do you want to know?

1019
00:56:08,905 --> 00:56:10,950
What do you write about
in your notebook?

1020
00:56:10,994 --> 00:56:12,299
What do you say in therapy?

1021
00:56:12,343 --> 00:56:14,301
[chuckles]:
I don't go to therapy.

1022
00:56:14,345 --> 00:56:16,565
-Well, maybe you should.
-[chuckles]

1023
00:56:16,608 --> 00:56:18,567
[Kenna laughs]

1024
00:56:24,224 --> 00:56:26,357
I write letters to Scotty.

1025
00:56:30,404 --> 00:56:32,102
Did you write about that night?

1026
00:56:38,238 --> 00:56:39,501
Yes.

1027
00:56:43,809 --> 00:56:47,378
-[button clicks]
-Uh, can you not play music?

1028
00:56:47,421 --> 00:56:48,771
Why?

1029
00:56:48,814 --> 00:56:50,773
I just-- I don't like it.

1030
00:56:50,816 --> 00:56:55,734
It's all... sad,
and everyone's in pain.

1031
00:56:55,778 --> 00:56:57,649
[chuckles]:
Okay.

1032
00:56:57,693 --> 00:56:59,346
Well, let's see.

1033
00:56:59,390 --> 00:57:03,829
♪ Jesus Christ,
I'm so blue all the time... ♪

1034
00:57:03,873 --> 00:57:05,483
See?

1035
00:57:05,527 --> 00:57:06,919
-That's sad.
-All right, let's...

1036
00:57:06,963 --> 00:57:08,007
[radio station changes]

1037
00:57:08,051 --> 00:57:09,922
♪ I'm all out of love ♪

1038
00:57:09,966 --> 00:57:11,358
♪ What am I without you... ♪

1039
00:57:11,402 --> 00:57:12,708
[Ledger laughs]

1040
00:57:12,751 --> 00:57:15,014
-There you go.
-[radio station changes]

1041
00:57:15,058 --> 00:57:18,714
-♪ So lo-o-o-onely ♪
-[both laughing]

1042
00:57:21,107 --> 00:57:22,979
♪ Lo-o-o-onely... ♪

1043
00:57:23,022 --> 00:57:24,676
[laughs]

1044
00:57:24,720 --> 00:57:27,505
